Tomtor (; ) is a rural locality (a selo) in Myuryunsky Rural Okrug of Ust-Aldansky District in the Sakha Republic, Russia, located  from Borogontsy, the administrative center of the district and the rural okrug. Its population as of the 2002 Census was 5.
